=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_LFSaw_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright mixed sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 439 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 438.7300
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.4696
  harmonic_regularity: 0.1291
  pitch_clarity: 28.6717
  inharmonicity: 0.1867
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -10.2467
  resonance_freq: 452.1973

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: LFSaw Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/LFSaw.html
// Tags: LFSaw, Classes, oscillator, modulation
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
{ LFSaw.ar(500, 1, 0.1) }.play

// used as both Oscillator and LFO:
{ LFSaw.ar(LFSaw.kr(4, 0, 200, 400), 0, 0.1) }.play
